gomodel:SYNGO_86  a       owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099055 replaced by GO:0045211" , "Rationale: Silver-enhanced immunogold-labeling of the Spine plasma membrane (Term not among the offered GO-Terms).\nfig. 2 C: Pooled measurements of 133 gold/ silver particles (from 38 randomly selected spine profiles) show that immunolabeling concentrates in a region 200 -300 nm away from the edge of the PSD. D: The same data, normalized to compensate for variable sizes of the spine profiles (as suggested by the ratio of the red\nline to the green line in cartoon; see Materials and Methods for equation). E: Gold/silver particles are at highest density at the spine tip (data normalized to compensate for variations in spine sizes, see\ncartoon).. Experimental description: \"Twelve male Sprague-Dawley rats (200 -350 g, Charles River, Raleigh, NC) were used for this study. p. 1128" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9377-7414" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9880-1214" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9681-3318" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0269-0311" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
